# Modifiable environment — the single place to override configurable values.
#
# Copy to `.env` and edit. Every tunable is namespaced by its agent's env prefix
# (e.g. SCANNER_, ANALYST_) and is bounds-checked on load, so an override cannot
# push a constant outside its safe range. The full catalogue — defaults,
# justifications, and bounds — is in docs/configuration.md.
#
# Nothing in this file is a secret store; secrets are provided out-of-band.

# ── Runtime infrastructure (P1+) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE_URL — relational store for the kernel persistence adapter.
# Defaults to local SQLite (sqlite:///./trading.db) so nothing external is
# needed; override with a Postgres URL in production. Leave unset to use SQLite.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@localhost:5432/trading
# NEO4J_URI=bolt://localhost:7687
# NEO4J_USER=neo4j
# NEO4J_PASSWORD=
# CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# ── Example agent tunables (illustrative — real ones land with each agent) ────
# SCANNER_MIN_RELATIVE_STRENGTH=0.0
# ANALYST_MIN_CONFIDENCE=0.6
# PORTFOLIO_MANAGER_MAX_POSITION_PCT=0.05
